post_text:
Skyview Adventure Connection students were challenged to build a pirate ship big enough for their group. Arrr!

One of the ways Adventure Connection is keeping students safe during the pandemic is to assign students to the same small groups for the whole summer. Groups rotate between a variety of spaces and activities, but groups do not interact with other groups. This isolates exposure risks while allowing students to have an enjoyable summer experience with friends in their group. #622Proud

post_text: Minnesota is now offering funds for families of children ages 5 to 18 who qualify for free or reduced-price school meals. The new program, called Pandemic EBT (P-EBT), will provide up to $325 per child that families can use to purchase nutritious food for their household. Approximately 350,000 Minnesota children could benefit. Learn more at: www.mn.p-ebt.org

post_text:
Starting Wednesday, March 18, District 622 students 18 years old and under can pick up bagged breakfast and lunch at Carver Elementary, Skyview Community School, and Richardson Elementary. All food must be taken to go and will be offered Monday-Friday while schools are closed due to COVID-19.

Meals will be distributed at the main entrance of three sites below between 9:30 - 11:00 a.m. (you will not need to get out of your vehicle). District 622 families may visit any pick-up site. A student must be present to pick-up the meals.

Later today, more information will be available online at www.isd622.org.

Breakfast and lunch pick-up sites are located at:

Carver Elementary: 2680 Upper Afton Rd, Maplewood, MN 55119

Richardson Elementary: 2400 17th Ave E, North St Paul, MN 55109

Skyview Community School: 1100 Heron Ave N, St Paul, MN 55128
